Biography

2015-16 (Senior): Had seven points and two assists against Newman (11/13)... Had a career high 25 points with two assists against Oklahoma Christian (11/14)... Scored 9 points against Colorado Mesa (11/20)... In the win against Western State (11/21), he scored 19 points and had 1 steal... He scored 14 points and had 2 rebounds against Dallas Christian (11/24)... In the big win against Drury (11/27), he scored 15 points and had 3 rebounds... Against Truman State (11/28), he scored 9 points and had 3 rebounds... In the win over Bacone (12/13), he had 14 points, 4 rebounds, and 2 assists... Had a team high 24 points, 5 rebounds, and 3 assists in the win against SW Adventists (12/19)... Against WT (12/31), he had 15 points, 3 rebounds, 3 assists, and 2 steals... Had a team high 15 points against Tarleton State (1/2)... In the win over Eastern NM (1/7), he scored 16 points, had 2 steals and 2 assists. Versus West Texas (1/10), he scored 10 points and had 2 rebounds... In the come back win over Texas A&M-Commerce (1/12), he had a team high 19 points, grabbed 4 rebounds, had 3 assists and 2 steals... Scored 13 points, grabbed 5 rebounds, and had 4 assists in the win over Angelo State (1/20)... In the win over Texas A&M-Kingsville (1/23), he scored 10 points and grabbed 8 rebounds... Scored 11 points, grabbed 4 rebounds, had 4 assists, and 1 block in the win over Midwestern (1/30)... Against Texas A&M-Commerce (2/3), he scored 17 points, had 2 steals and 1 block. He scored 10 points, had 5 rebounds, 3 assists and 3 steals in the win over Tarleton (2/6). In the win over ENMU (2/11), he scored 13 points, 4 rebounds, and one steal... Scored 15 points, grabbed 5 rebounds, and had 3 assists against Angelo State (2/17)... Against Kingsville (2/20), he scored 13 points, had 1 rebound and 1 assist... Scored 16 points and grabbed 3 rebounds against Midwestern State (2/27)...

2014-15 (Junior): Recorded 14 points, making four three pointers, grabbed six rebounds and had four assists off the bench in his first action as an Aggies against St. Gregory's (11/14)... Had 13 points and five rebounds in the win against USAO (11/15)... Hit three three pointers for nine points against NWOSU (11/22)... Made four three pointers and had a total of 14 points and one steal against Arkansas Tech (11/25)... Made 6 three pointers and had 20 points total along with 3 rebounds and one block against ECU (11/29)... Collected 9 points, 3 rebounds, and 1 assist against Bacone (12/16)... Scored 14 points and grabbed 2 rebounds in 31 minutes at Southern Nazarene (12/19)... Recorded 14 points and a career high 6 assists against DCC (12/20)... He started off the new year with 16 points against Northwestern (1/3)... Scored 16 points and grabbed 4 rebounds at West Texas A&M (1/10)... Hit 3 from behind the arc and scored 13 points total against A&M-Commerce (2/4)... Went 4-5 on three pointers and 2-2 from the free throw line with a total of 14 points against West Texas A&M (2/14)... Scored a career high 23 points going 6-8 on three pointers against Midwestern State (3/5).

Prior to Cameron: Sat out this past season at Colby Community College in Colby, Kansas. Previously averaged 5 ppg & 1.3 rpg while shooting 38% from downtown at FMU as a redshirt freshman.

Personal: Born Cameron Eugene Lee in Houston, TX.....Nickname is Cam......Graduated from Ridge View High School where he played for coach John Combs.....left-handed release.....Averaged 16 points, five rebounds and three assists per game his senior season.....Helped the Blazers to a spot in the AAAA state championship game.....He was honored with All-State and All-Region recognition
